messages.content: What is the purpose of comfyui-model-db?
The purpose of comfyui-model-db is to store settings by model in ComfyUI.
How can you add the Model DB node in ComfyUI?
To add the Model DB node in ComfyUI, you need to go to Add node > utils > Model DB.
How are settings saved in comfyui-model-db?
In comfyui-model-db, settings are saved with the current checkpoint and current time key as the ID.
Can you change the key name in comfyui-model-db?
No, you cannot change the key name in comfyui-model-db in order to simplify the process flow.
What are some of the output types available in comfyui-model-db?
Some of the output types available in comfyui-model-db include MODEL, CLIP, VAE, POSITIVE, NEGATIVE, SEED, CFG, SAMPLER_NAME, SCHEDULER, DENOISE, WIDTH, HEIGHT, and LATENT.
What is the data type of the output 'SEED' in comfyui-model-db?
The data type of the output 'SEED' in comfyui-model-db is INT.
What is the default key in comfyui-model-db?
The default key in comfyui-model-db is set to the last key of the model.
What are some of the updates made to comfyui-model-db?
Some of the updates made to comfyui-model-db include adding output latent, changing widget positions, and setting the default key to the last key of the model.
